<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.2.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-09-28T23:36:46+02:00</updated><id>/feed.xml</id><title type="html">A Blog by Petr Řehoř</title><author><name>Petr Řehoř</name></author><entry><title type="html">Microsoft Remote Desktop with Czech Keyboard</title><link href="/posts/2020/03/30/remote-desktop-with-czech-keyboard.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Microsoft Remote Desktop with Czech Keyboard" /><published>2020-03-30T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2020-03-30T00:00:00+02:00</updated><id>/posts/2020/03/30/remote-desktop-with-czech-keyboard</id><content type="html" xml:base="/posts/2020/03/30/remote-desktop-with-czech-keyboard.html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org&quot;&gt;Karabiner-Elements&lt;/a&gt; mappings (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/prehor/dotfiles/blob/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/microsoft-remote-desktop.json&quot;&gt;control keys&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/prehor/dotfiles/blob/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/microsoft-remote-desktop-czech.json&quot;&gt;czech language keys&lt;/a&gt;) that allow you to use the Apple macOS Czech keyboard layout in Windows when connected using Microsoft Remote Desktop.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Download the file &lt;a href=&quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/prehor/dotfiles/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/microsoft-remote-desktop.json&quot;&gt;microsoft-remote-desktop.json&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/prehor/dotfiles/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/microsoft-remote-desktop-czech.json&quot;&gt;microsoft-remote-desktop-czech.json&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;~/.config/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications&lt;/code&gt; folder.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;In the &lt;a href=&quot;https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org&quot;&gt;Karabiner-Elements&lt;/a&gt; preferences go to the &lt;strong&gt;Complex modifications&lt;/strong&gt; menu.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Add rule&lt;/strong&gt; and  enable rules in &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Remote Desktop&lt;/strong&gt; sections.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Enjoy Apple macOS czech keyboard in Windows remote desktop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><author><name>Petr Řehoř</name></author><category term="posts" /><category term="Apple" /><category term="macOS" /><category term="Remote Desktop" /><category term="Windows" /><summary type="html">Karabiner-Elements mappings that allow you to use the Apple macOS Czech keyboard layout in Windows when connected using Microsoft Remote Desktop.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Cmd-+ on Czech Keyboard</title><link href="/posts/2020/03/26/cmd-plus-on-czech-keyboard.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Cmd-+ on Czech Keyboard" /><published>2020-03-26T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2020-03-26T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/posts/2020/03/26/cmd-plus-on-czech-keyboard</id><content type="html" xml:base="/posts/2020/03/26/cmd-plus-on-czech-keyboard.html">&lt;p&gt;The MacBook Czech keyboard (and probably other European/ISO keyboards as well) lacks the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Cmd-+&lt;/code&gt; key used for &lt;strong&gt;Zoom In&lt;/strong&gt; in most applications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/prehor/dotfiles/blob/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/command%2Bnon_us_backslash.json&quot;&gt;Here&lt;/a&gt; is a complex modification for &lt;a href=&quot;https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org&quot;&gt;Karabiner-Elements&lt;/a&gt; that maps &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Cmd-&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt; key (at the left of key &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;1&lt;/code&gt;) to &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Cmd-+&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Download the file &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/prehor/dotfiles/blob/master/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications/command-%2B-czech.json&quot;&gt;command-+-czech.json&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;~/.config/karabiner/assets/complex_modifications&lt;/code&gt; folder.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;In the &lt;a href=&quot;https://karabiner-elements.pqrs.org&quot;&gt;Karabiner-Elements&lt;/a&gt; preferences go to the &lt;strong&gt;Complex modifications&lt;/strong&gt; menu.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;Add rule&lt;/strong&gt; and  enable rule in &lt;strong&gt;Command-+ on Czech (European/ISO) Keyboard&lt;/strong&gt; section.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Enjoy &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Cmd-+&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Cmd-&amp;lt;&lt;/code&gt; key (at the left of key &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;1&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><author><name>Petr Řehoř</name></author><category term="posts" /><category term="Apple" /><category term="macOS" /><summary type="html">The MacBook Czech keyboard (and probably other European/ISO keyboards as well) lacks the Cmd-+ key used for Zoom In in most applications.</summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Welcome!</title><link href="/posts/2020/03/22/welcome.html" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Welcome!" /><published>2020-03-22T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2020-03-22T00:00:00+01:00</updated><id>/posts/2020/03/22/welcome</id><content type="html" xml:base="/posts/2020/03/22/welcome.html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hello world&lt;/strong&gt;, this is my first blog post.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hope you like it!&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Petr Řehoř</name></author><category term="posts" /><summary type="html">Hello world, this is my first blog post.</summary></entry></feed>